Job Description:
Vacancy Intro
Royal Haskoning DHV is an independent consultancy that integrates 140 years of engineering expertise with digital technologies and software solutions.
As consulting engineers, we care deeply about our people, our clients, and society at large.
Through our mission Enhancing Society Together, we take responsibility for having a positive impact on the world. We constantly challenge ourselves and others to develop sustainable solutions to local and global issues related to the built environment.
What will you do
Job Description of MEP Engineer
Report to Head of Construction as line manager;
Report to Construction Manager on project level;
Organize and control/monitor activities of discipline supervisor;
Main contact on site in the absence of Construction Manager;
Organize daily coordination meeting and weekly meeting with all stakeholder on site, distribute minutes and agenda through document control;
Verification and signing the minutes of meeting and all correspondences related to the project;
Verify/Approve shop drawings, method statements, procedures, and other submissions and provide final approvals or recommendations to the Client, as required;
Verify/Approve material submittal with support of discipline engineer if required;
Verify/Approve and monitor material movements/transfer and quantity authorizations with support discipline supervisor;
Take part in material inspections and provide required recommendation to the Client;
Provide technical guidance related to current site activities and verify that relevant information were forwarded to discipline supervisor and to the Contractor;
Monitor progress of work and recommend/monitor rectification action;
Preparation of testing of works and verification of results and follow up;
Prepare/Verify the required reports (progress, inspection, review etc.);
Evaluate change order requests with support of discipline engineer if required and provide technical advice to Constrution Manager and Client on alternatives.
Preparation and monitoring completion of initial snag list issuing recommendation for final inspections handing over.
Preparing site instruction for CM to approved.
Prepare draft of Monthly report for CM regarding technical matters and quality.
Where you will work
Site Area
What you bring
Degree from Mechanical & Electrical Engineer
Proven 5+ years experiences as MEP Engineer/Site Engineer on site
Having experiences in MFG / Industries company such as F&B , Oleochemical , Pharmacheutical, etc.
Willing to Work on site.
What we offer you
Are you our new colleague?
Kindly apply by clicking the button below with your updated CV.
Acquisition by agencies is not appreciated.

